        He's working on raising the level of abstracton in diagnostics experiences for Visual Studio customers and also looks after T4 code generation.</p>
    <p>
        You can read his blog <a href="http://blogs.msdn.com/garethj">here</a>.</p>
    <p>
        Previously at Microsoft he worked on DSL Tools, the software factory initiative and Visual Studio eXtensibility.
